WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.000
Tommy Grant is a taxi driver in London. He works for TOP TAXIS.

00:05.000 --> 00:11.000
One day, Tommy's boss, Sam, telephones him. It is very early in the morning.

00:11.000 --> 00:16.000
Tommy, says Sam. Can you be at The Ritz Hotel at 9:00 o'clock?

00:16.000 --> 00:20.000
Yes, says Tommy, but why?

00:20.000 --> 00:25.000
Sam and his wife are having breakfast with their children, Billy and Katy.

00:25.000 --> 00:29.000
Gloria Brash is in London, says Sam.

00:29.000 --> 00:37.000
Gloria Brash! says Tommy. The film star! Where do you want me to drive her?

00:37.000 --> 00:41.000
Not her, says Sam. Him.

00:41.000 --> 00:47.000
Her 12-year-old son Dino wants to see London today. His mother's working.

00:47.000 --> 00:53.000
There's a letter for you at The Ritz. There's 50 pounds, too. That's for Dino.

00:53.000 --> 00:59.000
50 pounds for one day in London! says Tommy. That's a lot of money.

00:59.000 --> 01:06.000
I know, says Sam. Be very nice to the boy, Tommy, and don't be late.

01:06.000 --> 01:11.000
You know me, says Tommy. I'm always early.

01:11.000 --> 01:18.000
It is 8:45. Tommy is at The Ritz 15 minutes early. He goes to the desk.

01:18.000 --> 01:21.000
I'm from TOP TAXIS, he says.

01:21.000 --> 01:25.000
The woman behind the desk gives him the letter and the money.

01:25.000 --> 01:30.000
The letter says, It's Dino's first time in London.

01:30.000 --> 01:33.000
Please take him to all these places.

01:33.000 --> 01:41.000
One, Buckingham Palace. Two, Harrods. Three, the British Museum.

01:41.000 --> 01:51.000
OK, thinks Tommy. Now, is Dino here? I know I'm early, but he sees a boy in a chair.

01:51.000 --> 01:58.000
Hello, he says. Are you Dino? That's me, says the boy.

01:58.000 --> 02:04.000
Are you the driver from TOP TAXIS? Yes, answers Tommy. The boy stands up.

02:04.000 --> 02:10.000
OK, he says. Let's go. First, Tommy drives to Buckingham Palace.

02:10.000 --> 02:14.000
The home of the Queen. He stops the taxi.

02:27.000 --> 02:33.000
What are you doing? asks Dino. I don't want to see this old place.

02:33.000 --> 02:39.000
Tommy looks at him. But I, then he remembers Sam's words.

02:39.000 --> 02:43.000
Be very nice to the boy.

02:43.000 --> 02:51.000
OK, Dino, he says. Where do you want to go?

02:51.000 --> 02:55.000
Five minutes later, Tommy stops the taxi again.

02:55.000 --> 02:59.000
Is this the place? He asks. That's right, answers Dino.

02:59.000 --> 03:03.000
Can I have 20 pounds, please?

03:03.000 --> 03:09.000
But I don't think your mother. I want 20 pounds now.

03:09.000 --> 03:16.000
Tommy gives Dino the money. Then he sits in the car and waits.

03:16.000 --> 03:21.000
Three hours later, Dino comes back.

03:21.000 --> 03:27.000
Now, are you hungry? asks Tommy. Yes, I am, answers Dino. Very hungry.

03:27.000 --> 03:33.000
Tommy drives to Harrods. There's a very good restaurant in this shop, he says.

03:33.000 --> 03:37.000
I don't want to eat here! says Dino. I want to have lunch there.

03:37.000 --> 03:43.000
Where? asks Tommy. He looks across the road.

03:43.000 --> 03:48.000
Dino goes into the Big Burger Bar with another 20 pounds.

03:48.000 --> 03:53.000
He eats a mountain of food and drinks four milkshakes.

03:53.000 --> 03:58.000
Tommy eats his lunch in the taxi. 20 pounds for lunch! he thinks.

03:58.000 --> 04:01.000
I can buy a week's food with 20 pounds.

04:01.000 --> 04:05.000
He looks out of the window and eats another sandwich.

04:05.000 --> 04:09.000
An hour later, Dino comes out of the restaurant.

04:09.000 --> 04:13.000
Be very nice to the boy, thinks Tommy.

04:13.000 --> 04:17.000
Do you want to go to the British Museum now? he asks.

04:17.000 --> 04:22.000
OK, answers Dino. Tommy looks at him.

04:22.000 --> 04:26.000
Yes! Tommy is very happy. He drives to the British Museum and gives Dino 10 pounds.

04:26.000 --> 04:31.000
Thanks, says Dino. Wait here.

04:31.000 --> 04:39.000
Then he goes into a cinema across the road from the museum.

04:39.000 --> 04:42.000
At 4:15, Dino comes out of the cinema.

04:42.000 --> 04:47.000
Tommy's sitting in the cab. He's very angry.

04:52.000 --> 04:56.000
Where do you want to go now? he asks.

04:56.000 --> 05:01.000
Oh, back to The Ritz, I think, says Dino.

05:01.000 --> 05:07.000
I'm tired and I want to have a bath before dinner.

05:07.000 --> 05:11.000
Good, thinks Tommy. Tommy starts the car again.

05:11.000 --> 05:15.000
At 4:30, Tommy stops in front of the hotel.

05:15.000 --> 05:21.000
Here we are, he says. He opens the door for Dino.

05:21.000 --> 05:26.000
Then he sees a beautiful woman in a very expensive coat.

05:26.000 --> 05:31.000
She's walking out of The Ritz and she's looking at him.

05:31.000 --> 05:36.000
I know that woman, thinks Tommy.

05:36.000 --> 05:40.000
Then he remembers. Of course, it's Gloria Brash!

05:40.000 --> 05:43.000
Are you the man from TOP TAXIS? asks Gloria.

05:43.000 --> 05:50.000
Yes, says Tommy. Come with me, says the film star.

05:50.000 --> 05:53.000
She walks back into the hotel.

05:53.000 --> 05:55.000
There, Tommy sees a boy sitting in a chair. He looks very sad.

05:55.000 --> 05:57.000
This is Dino, she says.

05:57.000 --> 06:01.000
But, but Tommy can't speak.

06:01.000 --> 06:04.000
I am very angry, says Gloria.

06:04.000 --> 06:10.000
Tommy looks at the boy, at the film star, and at the young boy again.

06:10.000 --> 06:16.000
But this can't be Dino! he says.

06:16.000 --> 06:18.000
Young man, I know my son! answers Gloria.

06:18.000 --> 06:22.000
Now, where is my 50 pounds?

06:22.000 --> 06:28.000
Tommy's face goes white. He looks out of the window.

06:28.000 --> 06:32.000
His taxi is there, but Dino is not.

06:32.000 --> 06:37.000
It is 5:00 o'clock in the afternoon.

06:37.000 --> 06:40.000
Tommy's boss, Sam, is at home.

06:40.000 --> 06:45.000
He and his wife are having a cup of tea.

06:45.000 --> 06:50.000
The door opens and their son, Billy, walks in.

06:50.000 --> 06:53.000
Hello, Billy, says Sam. Good day at school?

06:53.000 --> 06:55.000
Billy looks very happy.

06:55.000 --> 06:58.000
Yes, thanks, he says. Very good.
